					Director seeks assault probation
				












Perelman directed the Oscar-nominated House of Sand and Fog





The director of Oscar-nominated film  The House of Sand and Fog, Vadim Perelman, is seeking  probation on assault charges.

The Ukrainian director, 42, is charged with groping two women and punching another at a Connecticut nightclub. The incident allegedly took place in July.

Perelman asked the state's Superior Court on Monday for a type of probation called accelerated rehabilitation.

If granted, he would have no criminal record upon completing the probation.


"Mr Perelman never intended to harm anyone during the evening in question," said his attorney, Paul Callan.

House of Sand and Fog was nominated for three Oscars in 2003, including a best actor for Sir Ben Kingsley.

However the film, which centres around the story of an Iranian immigrant to the US, failed to take home any awards.

The case was adjourned until 16 October.






